SIMPLE: wasteness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wasteness
<hw>Waste"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being waste; a desolate state or condition;
desolation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A day of trouble and distress, a day of <qex>wasteness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Zeph. i. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is waste; a desert; a waste.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Through woods and <qex>wasteness</qex> wide him daily sought.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waster</ent>⟦br⟧
